# Pinned llama.cpp release (github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp) for llama-server.
# Three non-comment lines below: <build-tag>, <cpu-tar-sha256>,
# <vulkan-tar-sha256>.
#
# ACQUISITION STRATEGY (owner decision):
#   * NVIDIA GPU box (nvidia-smi >=8000 MB VRAM): BUILD llama.cpp from SOURCE
#     with CUDA at the pinned tag (primary path). No prebuilt sha is needed for
#     the CUDA path — the source is fetched via `git clone --branch <tag>`, and
#     the compute capability is pinned in the installer (RTX 2000 Ada = sm_89).
#     If the source build fails (no CUDA toolkit installable, clone/compile
#     error) the installer FALLS BACK to the Vulkan prebuilt below.
#   * No GPU / VRAM <8000 MB: download the CPU prebuilt (the floor).
# llama.cpp stopped shipping prebuilt Linux CUDA binaries — the release only
# has Windows CUDA — which is why CUDA is a source build here. The two shas
# below are the CPU and Vulkan prebuilt fallbacks, and both are .tar.gz (gzip
# tarballs, extracted with tar — the prebuilt archive format changed from the
# earlier release); the installer verifies each against its sha before extract.
#
# EXECUTION-TIME STEP (refresh the two shas whenever the pin changes — they
# cannot be known at authoring time; the installer hard-fails if a sha is left
# unpinned / is not a 64-hex-char digest):
